566
00:33:57,915 --> 00:34:00,648
That freighter was hijacked by pirates
in international waters,

567
00:34:00,693 --> 00:34:02,760
but it was rescued
by the escorting Chinese Navy.

568
00:34:06,300 --> 00:34:07,300
Alright. Got it.

569
00:34:08,500 --> 00:34:09,060
Okay.

570
00:34:09,060 --> 00:34:10,820
Keep in touch. Bye.

571
00:34:20,293 --> 00:34:21,940
I know you've been through a lot lately.

572
00:34:23,660 --> 00:34:24,500
At first,

573
00:34:24,893 --> 00:34:26,709
I wanted to wait
until you felt a bit better,

574
00:34:26,710 --> 00:34:28,600
rested up, before asking you out.

575
00:34:29,950 --> 00:34:31,620
Besides, I've been thinking
a lot lately.

576
00:34:32,340 --> 00:34:33,100
So...

577
00:34:34,140 --> 00:34:35,100
There's something

578
00:34:35,715 --> 00:34:37,315
I've been holding in this whole time.

579
00:34:39,500 --> 00:34:41,220
Why so serious all of a sudden?

580
00:34:44,140 --> 00:34:45,020
Do you remember

581
00:34:46,540 --> 00:34:48,300
what I told you

582
00:34:48,360 --> 00:34:49,871
before you left for the Roman Islands?

583
00:34:51,300 --> 00:34:52,060
I said

584
00:34:52,093 --> 00:34:54,093
you should report it
to the relevant authorities.

585
00:34:54,220 --> 00:34:55,060
Do you remember that?

586
00:34:55,500 --> 00:34:56,220
I do.

587
00:34:59,020 --> 00:35:00,100
I did report it.

588
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:02,220
I even got permission from Mr. Tian.

589
00:35:02,260 --> 00:35:04,026
I only made my way there
with his approval.

590
00:35:04,220 --> 00:35:05,820
And I wasn't alone.

591
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:07,060
I took Hai with me.

592
00:35:08,500 --> 00:35:10,060
Well, you know what I'm trying to say.

593
00:35:11,020 --> 00:35:12,580
And I'm not joking.

594
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:14,580
I don't get what you mean.

595
00:35:15,020 --> 00:35:16,500
And I'm not joking either.

596
00:35:21,740 --> 00:35:22,620
Captain Wu.

597
00:35:24,500 --> 00:35:25,940
Let's just get down to business.

598
00:35:25,980 --> 00:35:28,100
You don't have to lecture me like that.

599
00:35:28,340 --> 00:35:29,540
I'm not lecturing you.

600
00:35:31,140 --> 00:35:32,260
I just felt lucky.

601
00:35:33,893 --> 00:35:36,170
It was lucky that I ran into you
on that stretch of ocean.

602
00:35:36,226 --> 00:35:37,937
Did you know how many merchant ships

603
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:40,140
need a naval escort
through that sea every day?

604
00:35:41,671 --> 00:35:43,620
Just one minor accident
and we'd have missed you.

605
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:48,340
What if we had?

606
00:35:49,982 --> 00:35:51,940
It really was a coincidence
you met the warship.

607
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:54,540
However, I really can't guarantee

608
00:35:55,260 --> 00:35:56,220
I'll be there by chance

609
00:35:56,220 --> 00:35:57,620
when you're in danger.

610
00:35:58,137 --> 00:35:59,540
Nor can I guarantee to be there

611
00:36:00,700 --> 00:36:02,220
whenever you need me.

612
00:36:03,940 --> 00:36:04,980
I'm not blaming you.

613
00:36:06,540 --> 00:36:08,420
I just hope that you
give it a good thought

614
00:36:09,180 --> 00:36:10,820
before you act after this.

615
00:36:11,900 --> 00:36:13,580
I know you're worried about me.

616
00:36:14,980 --> 00:36:16,460
But I need you to believe

617
00:36:17,500 --> 00:36:19,340
that I know exactly what I'm doing.

618
00:36:20,740 --> 00:36:22,780
I've been an investigative journalist
for years.

619
00:36:24,900 --> 00:36:26,660
I'm willing to accept
the risks that come

620
00:36:26,660 --> 00:36:27,940
with the profession of my choice.

621
00:36:28,020 --> 00:36:30,140
But what you did was irresponsible.

622
00:36:40,790 --> 00:36:42,340
I'm aware of the nature of your work.

623
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,900
And I know what your intentions are.

624
00:36:46,448 --> 00:36:48,337
I have great respect
for your professionalism.

625
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:49,700
But only by

626
00:36:49,740 --> 00:36:51,340
ensuring your safety

627
00:36:51,980 --> 00:36:53,660
can you do your job better.

628
00:36:55,293 --> 00:36:56,820
If you report it to the authorities,

629
00:36:57,071 --> 00:36:58,580
you can still operate independently.

630
00:36:59,180 --> 00:37:00,980
And you'll have solid safety backup

631
00:37:01,260 --> 00:37:02,940
for your solo operations.

632
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,420
Do you not understand
what "reporting" means?

633
00:37:10,740 --> 00:37:11,860
Let me explain it to you.

634
00:37:12,660 --> 00:37:14,580
When we're on the front lines,

635
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:17,340
our backup supplies
are what keep us strong.

636
00:37:18,260 --> 00:37:20,620
They know our exact
coordinates and position, so...

637
00:37:20,620 --> 00:37:22,330
I don't need to know
anything about backup,

638
00:37:22,337 --> 00:37:23,460
supplies, and positions.

639
00:37:23,460 --> 00:37:25,100
I'm an investigative journalist.

640
00:37:25,940 --> 00:37:26,700
Our job

641
00:37:26,700 --> 00:37:27,980
isn't like your beach landings,

642
00:37:27,980 --> 00:37:29,190
which are the more the merrier.

643
00:37:29,260 --> 00:37:30,820
Listen, since I entered this field,

644
00:37:30,820 --> 00:37:33,180
I've completed many investigations
all by myself.

645
00:37:33,180 --> 00:37:34,340
That's how our industry works.

646
00:37:34,340 --> 00:37:35,309
The more people who know,

647
00:37:35,310 --> 00:37:36,804
the more likely things get screwed up.

648
00:37:42,100 --> 00:37:43,340
Fine, Captain Wu.

649
00:37:44,420 --> 00:37:45,620
If you think

650
00:37:45,620 --> 00:37:46,940
I'm being a lone wolf

651
00:37:46,980 --> 00:37:48,260
who tries to show off,

652
00:37:49,980 --> 00:37:51,100
suit yourself.

653
00:37:51,293 --> 00:37:53,115
- I'm really not...
- Thank you for saving me.

654
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:56,420
Tang Xin.

655
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:18,180
Fate has certainly played a trick on us.

656
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:23,820
Dad.

657
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:28,426
I think there's more than meets the eye

658
00:38:28,448 --> 00:38:30,380
with Yuhang's visit
to the Roman Islands.

659
00:38:31,260 --> 00:38:32,260
It wasn't just

660
00:38:32,260 --> 00:38:34,460
about chasing after that reporter
like he said.

661
00:38:36,020 --> 00:38:37,180
Then what do you think?

662
00:38:40,020 --> 00:38:41,340
I think

663
00:38:42,900 --> 00:38:44,980
he found out something about our family.

664
00:38:47,340 --> 00:38:48,020
Dad.

665
00:38:48,580 --> 00:38:50,220
We must stop them
from seeing each other.

666
00:38:50,471 --> 00:38:53,093
What if Tang Xin manages to talk him
into collaborating with her?

667
00:38:53,700 --> 00:38:55,940
You think telling him
to stop seeing her will work?

668
00:38:57,180 --> 00:38:58,220
It's not that serious.

669
00:38:58,740 --> 00:39:00,420
Even if he knows something,

670
00:39:01,060 --> 00:39:02,820
it's just scratching the surface.

671
00:39:03,420 --> 00:39:05,740
Besides, we're a family.

672
00:39:06,020 --> 00:39:07,660
Even if he knows something,

673
00:39:07,660 --> 00:39:08,820
so what?

674
00:39:09,540 --> 00:39:11,460
But this won't hold up for long.

675
00:39:14,020 --> 00:39:16,260
Maybe I should get someone

676
00:39:17,420 --> 00:39:18,340
to...

677
00:39:20,380 --> 00:39:21,500
Right now,

678
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:24,540
the real danger isn't that woman.

679
00:39:26,060 --> 00:39:28,620
It's whoever has been feeding her leads.

680
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:30,740
I've been trying
to track that person down.

681
00:39:31,540 --> 00:39:34,020
But with just an email address,
it's tough.

682
00:39:37,020 --> 00:39:37,900
Look.

683
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:41,740
Only a handful of people

684
00:39:43,180 --> 00:39:44,180
know our secrets.

685
00:39:44,540 --> 00:39:45,140
Indeed.

686
00:39:45,940 --> 00:39:47,900
Start by screening

687
00:39:48,140 --> 00:39:50,420
the innermost circle.

688
00:39:55,715 --> 00:39:57,004
Are you tired from walking?

689
00:39:57,740 --> 00:39:58,460
A little.

690
00:39:58,715 --> 00:39:59,660
Let's take some rest.

691
00:40:06,340 --> 00:40:07,020
Here.

692
00:40:08,060 --> 00:40:09,220
Let me rub your legs.

693
00:40:14,980 --> 00:40:15,620
Sore?

694
00:40:21,060 --> 00:40:21,820
Honey.

695
00:40:23,180 --> 00:40:24,620
Do you remember

696
00:40:24,740 --> 00:40:26,980
the first time we came to this park?

697
00:40:28,860 --> 00:40:29,900
Of course I do.

698
00:40:29,980 --> 00:40:31,580
We had our very first date

699
00:40:31,620 --> 00:40:32,460
right here.

700
00:40:32,900 --> 00:40:34,260
You had an interview that day.

701
00:40:34,493 --> 00:40:36,060
But you started whining to me instead.

702
00:40:39,580 --> 00:40:41,420
And after all that whining,

703
00:40:41,980 --> 00:40:43,500
I still didn't even get the job.

704
00:40:44,380 --> 00:40:45,620
I failed to land the lab,

705
00:40:46,620 --> 00:40:48,140
but I ended up getting married.

706
00:40:48,900 --> 00:40:50,860
That was the smartest decision
you ever made.

707
00:40:55,220 --> 00:40:57,100
Feels like
it all just happened yesterday.

708
00:41:25,900 --> 00:41:26,820
Have some water.

709
00:41:45,060 --> 00:41:45,740
Honey.

710
00:41:47,180 --> 00:41:48,620
Let's keep walking a bit more.

711
00:41:51,660 --> 00:41:52,380
Sure.

712
00:41:56,860 --> 00:41:57,500
Come on.

713
00:42:11,300 --> 00:42:14,780
♪The vast sky and sea,
